getInfo

public Image getInfo()
              throws SmugmugException
Description copied from interface: ISmugObject
Obtains detailed information from the repository or cache for this object. Some objects require a password to obtain (part of) this detailed information (see setObjectPassword). The level of detail is determined by the current session-account. The owner of this object gets all the information. Any other account may only get part of the object's data.

getInfoURLsOnly

public Image getInfoURLsOnly(AlbumTemplatePrototype.Data.VIEW_STYLE viewStyle)
                      throws SmugmugException
Retrieves information, from the Smugmug repository, about the URLs of this image only. All this object's attributes ending in 'URL' are changed after calling this method (e.g. AlbumURL, OriginalURL, MediumURL, etc.).

update

public Image update()
             throws SmugmugException
Description copied from interface: ISmugObject
If this object has changed, the changes will be sent to the Smugmug repository. Only owners of this object can update the object.

Specified by:
update in interface ISmugObject<Image>
Returns:
this.
Throws:
SmugmugException
See Also:

This method may reposition the image within the album (Position has changed), may update the raw image data (MD5Sum has changed), move the image to another album (AlbumID or Album has changed) and/or change the caption/keywords of this image.

write

public void write(java.io.OutputStream os,
                  Image.IMAGE_SIZE size)
           throws SmugmugException
Writes the image-data of this image to the specified output-stream. If the ImageData attribute is a byte-array of more than 0 bytes, this data will be written. If ImageData is not set, the image-data is fetched from the image's URL given the image-size (@see getURL(String)).

Parameters:
os - The target output-stream.
size - Determines the 'size' of the image-URL. If set to null, the getLargestSizeURL() is used instead.
Throws:
SmugmugException
